Description: Signal position evaluation of analogencoder inoperativeParameter _WarnLatched Bit 16
Cause: Incorrect encoder wiring.Encoder hardware interfaceinoperative.

Description: Error detected with quasi absolutepositionParameter _SigLatched Bit 16
Cause: The motor shaft may have beenmoved while the drive was powereddown. A quasi absolute position hasbeen detected that is not within thepermissible motor shaft deviationrange.
Correctives: If the quasi absolute function isactive, only power down the drive ifthe motor is at a standstill and do notmove the motor shaft when the driveis off.

Description: Index pulse is not available for theencoderParameter _WarnLatched Bit 16
Error in analog signals from encoderdetected. Additional information inthe error memory indicates Internal_DeltaQuep.Parameter _SigLatched Bit 16
Cause: Encoder cable not properlyconnected.Encoder signals subject to EMI(shield connection, wiring, etc.).Mechanical issue.
Correctives: Verify EMC measures.Contact your Schneider Electricservice representative.
